rComments: Although this class at times may be challenging Professor Denney goes through concepts clearly and asks whether the class understands these concepts before he continues lecturing. He is very accessible outside of class and tutorials are very useful in practicing using R studio.

He was an incredible instructor, he was energetic and encouraging to all of his students in a way you don't really see with most profs. If you asked a question, he genuinely cared to answer it, and while he struggled to sometimes (because most poli sci students aren't used to this material), he genuinely wanted everyone to understand the course.

Professor Steven is a great teacher who cares about student's learning process. If you ask any question regarding of class material, he will definitely help you out. He creates a better learning classroom environment.

rComments: This course is not as awful as it is made out to be, although it is more difficult than your average political science course because you have to incorporate some basic stats. The course overall is one that will help you in the real world and towards your job so it is recommended to take. This course gives you another thinking cap. TA is horrible.
He is terrible at explaining concepts, and gives u bad grades. Save yourself, don't take this course

The course is no about coding and its not that awful. It's about statistical data - how to collect it and how to analyze it in Political Science. We learn how to use R Studio, a very useful tool for research work opportunities in the future.
